  "summary": "Zombies",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "Zombies stand still on a campfire and freeze up n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Create a new Survival world with default settings.\n2. Gather resources to craft a campfire using 3 sticks and 3 pieces of charcoal or wood.\n3. Place the campfire on the ground in a flat area.\n4. Switch to Creative mode to easily summon zombies.\n5. Use the command '/summon minecraft:zombie' to spawn a zombie near the campfire.\n6. Observe the zombie as it approaches the campfire.\n7. Note that the zombie stands still on the campfire and does not move or take damage. \n8. Wait for a few minutes to confirm that the zombie remains frozen in place on the campfire.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 1.21.8",
  "Observed Behavior": "When a zombie comes into contact with a campfire, it exhibits an unexpected behavior where it stands still and becomes unresponsive. This occurs regardless of whether the campfire is lit or extinguished. The zombie does not attempt to move away from the campfire, nor does it engage in any other typical zombie behaviors such as attacking players or pathfinding. \n\n:\n1. Spawn or locate a zombie in a Minecraft world.\n2. Place a campfire (either lit or unlit) in proximity to the zombie.\n3. Observe the zombie's behavior as it approaches the campfire.\n\n:\nZombies should be able to navigate around campfires, avoiding them as they would with other hazards, such as lava or cacti. Instead, they should either move away from the campfire or continue their pursuit of nearby players or villagers without freezing.\n\n#### Additional Notes:\n- This issue appears to affect all variants of zombies.\n- The freezing behavior persists until the zombie is either removed from the vicinity of the campfire or the campfire is destroyed.\n- This bug does not seem to affect other mobs in the same way; for example, skeletons and creepers do not exhibit this behavior when near a campfire. \n\nThis bug could potentially disrupt gameplay, particularly in survival scenarios where players rely on mob behavior for strategic planning.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When a zombie stands on a campfire, it should take damage from the fire and attempt to move away from it, as zombies are programmed to avoid fire and other sources of damage. The expected behavior is that the zombie would exhibit its normal pathfinding behavior, which includes moving away from harmful blocks like campfires to seek safety or pursue nearby players. If a zombie is unable to move due to being blocked or other environmental factors, it should still attempt to find a way to escape the fire instead of freezing in place. This aligns with the game's mechanics where zombies actively avoid fire damage.",
